Good presentation techniques depend on many factors such as form, content, technology and delivery, constraints and user feedback. Good presentation techniques can be defined below.

Form - Give a presentation based on a frame of screen and having good ideas for how to use screen time to present relevant content or have audience feedback for specific purpose as a part of it. Categorise as categories, e.g. ideas, ideas;

Art - Obstruct the flow of the presentation by blocking important areas of interest in question and exposing the audience to different perspectives, thus reducing opportunities for improvised content or scenebuilding or audience participation. Agree on harsh
